commit.message:
Update Travis CI configuration

Get rid of outdated Debian packages, switch to the container based
infrastructure and use Flycheck’s Emacs build scripts to build Emacs on
Travis CI.

Increase version coverage, and cache Cask directories.

commit.message:
Call url-retrieve-synchronously with a single argument only

Fix Emacs 24.3 compatibility
Add functions to query MELPA recipes

Do not test against Emacs 23 anymore

Cask dropped Emacs 23 support, and it's more hassle than it is worth
now.
Change issue references to avoid conflicts with md syntax

Convert remaining files to markdown

It's the standard, let's get over it
Make headings compatible with Outline Mode
Do not require byte-compilation for tests
Do not load outdated byte code in tests
